    <header class="article-header pt-3 pb-8" id="article-top">
      <h1 title="Automation?" class="text-3xl font-medium leading-tight">
        Automation?
        
        
        

            

            
            
        
      </h1>

      <div class="article-author pt-4">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <div class="avatar article-avatar">
            
            <img src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b01d445686bf0c066c47cc5552d995e7?default=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.zendesk.com%2Fhc%2Fassets%2Fdefault_avatar.png&amp;r=g" alt="Avatar" class="user-avatar h-16 rounded-full" />
          </div>
          <div class="article-meta pl-3 pb-1">
            
              Oskar Sigurdsson
              <a class="post-subscribe" title="Opens a sign-in dialog" rel="nofollow" role="button" data-auth-action="signin" data-follower-count="12" aria-selected="false" href="/hc/en-us/community/posts/207381125-Automation-/subscription.html">Follow</a>
            <div class="article-updated meta-data text-regular text-sm">Updated <time datetime="2020-12-29T15:20:00Z" title="2020-12-29T15:20:00Z" data-datetime="relative">December 29, 2020 15:20</time></div>
             		<div class="post-published meta text-regular text-sm">
                  <time datetime="2016-05-04T18:53:11Z" title="2016-05-04T18:53:11Z" data-datetime="calendar">May 04, 2016 18:53</time>
                </div>
             

              
            </div>
        </div> 
      </div>
    </header>
    
    

    <section class="article-info">
      <div class="article-content">
        <main class="article article-body text-justify">
          <p>I would appreciate if you could automate the plugin from within your Daw. It would be very nice to be able to flick the mono switch with a controller or keyboard button, switch from speaker calibration to headphone etc. Can this be added pretty please ? :Þ</p>
        </main>

      </div>
    </section>

