                <section class="comment-body"><p>Hi Daniel, thanks for your input and apologies for the huge post-approval time!</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Yes, this is only available for hard-bypass within the given DAW MIDI mapping functionality. Advanced MIDI mapping for Reference is currently only available for the Systemwide app, not for the plugin. You can actually take advantage if you use the Systemwide app as your DAW output. More on that here: <a href="/hc/en-us/search/click?data=BAh7CzoHaWRsKwiHsl3SUwA6D2FjY291bnRfaWRpA1xGCjoJdHlwZUkiDGFydGljbGUGOgZFVDoIdXJsSSJdaHR0cHM6Ly9zdXBwb3J0LnNvbmFyd29ya3MuY29tL2hjL2VuLXVzL2FydGljbGVzLzM2MDAxMTY0MTQ3OS1NSURJLW1hcHBpbmctaW4tU3lzdGVtd2lkZQY7CFQ6DnNlYXJjaF9pZEkiKWYwOTM5YjJjLTNmMDEtNDZjYi1hMzg0LWUwOTM3MWQ2ZmE4NwY7CEY6CXJhbmtpBg%3D%3D--af48794a7d5aa00cb7ff856bc8cf57c403580a42" rel="nofollow noreferrer">MIDI mapping in Systemwide</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>MIDI mapping for the plugin might be possible for the next major release, but not within Reference 4. </p></section>
              </div>

